definition.value: A monocarboxylic acid that is phenylacetic acid in which the hydrogen at position 3 on the benzene ring is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A dimethoxyflavone that is flavone carrying hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7, and 8, and methoxy groups at positions 4' and 6.
A monoterpenoid consisting of two prenyl units linked head-to-tail and functionalised with a hydroxy group at its tail end.
